                            <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">ðŸ”’ Privacy Policy</h1>
                            <p class="text-gray-600">HIPAA-compliant data protection and privacy practices</p>
                            <div class="mt-4 text-sm text-gray-500">Effective Date: January 1, 2024 | Version 1.0</div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="prose max-w-none">
                            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">1. Information We Collect</h2>
                            
                            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">1.1 Protected Health Information (PHI)</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">As a HIPAA-covered entity, we collect and process PHI including:</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-4 space-y-2">
                                <li>Client demographic information (name, date of birth, address)</li>
                                <li>Medical history and current health status</li>
                                <li>Treatment needs and ASAM level assessments</li>
                                <li>Insurance information and coverage details</li>
                                <li>Referral and placement history</li>
                            </ul>

                            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">1.2 User Account Information</h3>
                            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-4 space-y-2">
                                <li>Professional credentials and licensing information</li>
                                <li>Organization affiliation and role</li>
                                <li>Contact information (email, phone)</li>
                                <li>System usage and activity logs</li>
                            </ul>

                            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">1.3 Technical Information</h3>
                            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-6 space-y-2">
                                <li>IP addresses and device identifiers</li>
                                <li>Browser type and version</li>
                                <li>System performance and error logs</li>
                                <li>Security event logs</li>
                            </ul>

                            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">2. How We Use Information</h2>
                            
                            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">2.1 Primary Uses</h3>
                            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-4 space-y-2">
                                <li><strong>Treatment Coordination:</strong> Facilitating appropriate referrals and placements</li>
                                <li><strong>Care Management:</strong> Supporting continuity of care across providers</li>
                                <li><strong>Quality Improvement:</strong> Analyzing outcomes to improve referral processes</li>
                                <li><strong>Compliance:</strong> Meeting regulatory and accreditation requirements</li>
                            </ul>

                            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">2.2 Secondary Uses</h3>
                            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-6 space-y-2">
                                <li>System administration and security monitoring</li>
                                <li>Performance analytics and reporting</li>
                                <li>Research and development (de-identified data only)</li>
                                <li>Legal compliance and audit purposes</li>
                            </ul>

                            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">3. HIPAA Compliance</h2>
                            
                            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">3.1 Business Associate Agreements</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">All covered entities using The Moment Connect must execute a Business Associate Agreement (BAA) that includes:</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-4 space-y-2">
                                <li>Permitted uses and disclosures of PHI</li>
                                <li>Safeguarding requirements and security measures</li>
                                <li>Breach notification procedures</li>
                                <li>Individual rights and access procedures</li>
                            </ul>

                            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">3.2 Security Safeguards</h3>
                            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-6 space-y-2">
                                <li><strong>Administrative:</strong> Security officer, workforce training, access management</li>
                                <li><strong>Physical:</strong> Secure data centers, workstation controls, media controls</li>
                                <li><strong>Technical:</strong> Encryption, access controls, audit logs, transmission security</li>
                            </ul>

                            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">4. Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
                            
                            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">4.1 Authorized Disclosures</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">PHI may be shared with:</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-4 space-y-2">
                                <li>Authorized healthcare providers involved in treatment</li>
                                <li>Insurance companies for payment purposes</li>
                                <li>Quality assurance and accreditation organizations</li>
                                <li>Legal authorities when required by law</li>
                            </ul>

                            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">4.2 Minimum Necessary Standard</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">We follow the minimum necessary standard, sharing only the information required for the specific purpose of the disclosure.</p>

                            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">5. Individual Rights</h2>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Under HIPAA, individuals have the right to:</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-6 space-y-2">
                                <li><strong>Access:</strong> Request copies of their PHI</li>
                                <li><strong>Amendment:</strong> Request corrections to their PHI</li>
                                <li><strong>Restriction:</strong> Request limits on use or disclosure</li>
                                <li><strong>Accounting:</strong> Receive a list of disclosures</li>
                                <li><strong>Notification:</strong> Be notified of breaches affecting their PHI</li>
                            </ul>

                            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">6. Data Retention</h2>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">We retain data according to the following schedule:</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-6 space-y-2">
                                <li><strong>Active Referrals:</strong> Retained while case is active</li>
                                <li><strong>Completed Referrals:</strong> 7 years from completion date</li>
                                <li><strong>Audit Logs:</strong> 6 years minimum</li>
                                <li><strong>User Account Data:</strong> 3 years after account closure</li>
                            </ul>

                            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">7. Breach Notification</h2>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">In the event of a data breach involving PHI:</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-6 space-y-2">
                                <li>Covered entities will be notified within 24 hours</li>
                                <li>Affected individuals will be notified within 60 days</li>
                                <li>HHS will be notified within 60 days</li>
                                <li>Media notification if breach affects 500+ individuals in a state</li>
                            </ul>

                            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">8. Contact Information</h2>
